<p><m>\therefore a=\frac{1}{3} \ln 8=\ln 2</m></p>

<p>求 (1) <m>\displaystyle\lim _{x \rightarrow 0}(1+3 x)^{\frac{1}{\sin x}}</m>; (2) <m>\displaystyle\lim _{x \rightarrow 0}\left(\cos ^{2} x\right)^{\frac{1}{\sin ^{2} x}}</m>;</p>

<p>解:(1) <m>\displaystyle \lim _{x \rightarrow 0}(1+3 x)^{\frac{1}{\sin x}}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0}\left[(1+3 x)^{\frac{1}{3 x}}\right]^{\frac{3 x}{\sin x}}=\mathrm{e}^{3} </m>.</p>

<p>(2)
\ltme\gt
\lim _{x \rightarrow 0}\left(\cos ^{2} x\right)^{\frac{1}{\sin ^{2} x}}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 0}\left(1-\sin ^{2} x\right)^{\frac{1}{\sin ^{2} x}} 
\xlongequal{t=\sin^2x}\lim _{t \rightarrow 0}(1-t)^{\frac{1}{t}}=\mathrm{e}^{-1}
